response.Q0: I just wanted to see the edge values more than anything because I saw that they were the highest. I focused mainly on those so, if I pressed on a node and it was over 40, I would go to that one without checking the other 4 nodes to get there
response.Q1: At the start, I didn't really understand what pressing the nodes did, I thought the money added or taken away was the value of the node but after a few games realised my mistake. That meant I did improve overtime as I picked up the proper strategy. I did read the instructions and thought I understood them but I obviously didn't take them in as much as I thought I had
response.Q2: The unpredictability made it hard for me to improve my performance. I did come to realise that the first 3 inner nodes nearly always gave an extra $0.25 so I made sure to press those every time. Trying to find a pattern in the outer nodes was difficult for me and I didn't find any patterns of those in the end

response.Q0: I did find it hard to understand that the cash number that came up after pressing a node wasn't linked to the actual value of the node. I was so focused on the green or red values that for a few rounds at the start I didn't notice the actual node value that appeared for those 3 seconds though I did soon see my mistake
